61, \"to\": 1783, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1622, \"end\": 1635, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.999999999994543, \"rank\": 5.0215125052012744e-12, \"text\": \"Great Britain\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 1655, \"end\": 1672, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/LEN_European_Aquatics_Championships\", \"score\": 0.977824471758845, \"rank\": 0.022678434506289608, \"text\": \"European champion\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/LEN_European_Aquatics_Championships\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/LEN_European_Aquatics_Championships\"}, {\"begin\": 1673, \"end\": 1689, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dina_Asher-Smith\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Dina Asher-Smith\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dina_Asher-Smith\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dina_Asher-Smith\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the first of three heats\", \"from\": 1499, \"to\": 1523}, {\"ngram\": \"3:35.83\", \"from\": 1527, \"to\": 1534}, {\"ngram\": \"his place\", \"from\": 1543, \"to\": 1552}, {\"ngram\": \"Sunday evening's semis\", \"from\": 1556, \"to\": 1578}, {\"ngram\": \"an afternoon\", \"from\": 1582, \"to\": 1594}, {\"ngram\": \"their 100m\", \"from\": 1704, \"to\": 1714}, {\"ngram\": \"the first day\", \"from\": 1724, \"to\": 1737}, {\"ngram\": \"track and field action\", \"from\": 1741, \"to\": 1763}, {\"ngram\": \"Stade de France\", \"from\": 1767, \"to\": 1782}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Kerr, who beat the Norwegian to the world title in 2023, was aware of - but utterly unfazed by - comments made by Ingebrigtsen, the reigning Olympic champion, who speaking to his country's media on Thursday said of the Scotsman: \\\"It is difficult to refer to him as a rival when he is never there.\", \"from\": 1785, \"to\": 2081, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1804, \"end\": 1813, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Norway\", \"score\": 0.9999997001569222, \"rank\": 2.983614077128359e-07, \"text\": \"Norwegian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Norway\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Norway\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Kerr\", \"from\": 1785, \"to\": 1789}, {\"ngram\": \"the world title\", \"from\": 1817, \"to\": 1832}, {\"ngram\": \"comments\", \"from\": 1882, \"to\": 1890}, {\"ngram\": \"Ingebrigtsen\", \"from\": 1899, \"to\": 1911}, {\"ngram\": \"the reigning Olympic champion\", \"from\": 1913, \"to\": 1942}, {\"ngram\": \"his country's media\", \"from\": 1960, \"to\": 1979}, {\"ngram\": \"Thursday\", \"from\": 1983, \"to\": 1991}, {\"ngram\": \"the Scotsman\", \"from\": 2000, \"to\": 2012}, {\"ngram\": \"a rival\", \"from\": 2050, \"to\": 2057}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He is known as the Brit who never competes.\\\"\", \"from\": 2082, \"to\": 2126, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the Brit\", \"from\": 2097, \"to\": 2105}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But Kerr, a bear who refused to be poked, said: \\\"I have heard.\", \"from\": 2128, \"to\": 2190, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Kerr\", \"from\": 2132, \"to\": 2136}, {\"ngram\": \"a bear\", \"from\": 2138, \"to\": 2144}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I would like to be defined in my career at the end of it, (and) I think I am just getting started.\", \"from\": 2191, \"to\": 2289, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"my career\", \"from\": 2221, \"to\": 2230}, {\"ngram\": \"the end\", \"from\": 2234, \"to\": 2241}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Hopefully that's medals, fast times and fun battles head-to-heads.\", \"from\": 2291, \"to\": 2358, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"medals\", \"from\": 2309, \"to\": 2315}, {\"ngram\": \"fast times\", \"from\": 2317, \"to\": 